author: @orangefruit12
text: People are free to express their opinions and there is nothing wrong with that, as long as you are not dragging other names down. But for me, Blackpink is the best girl group the world has ever had. Millions of fans from around the world think so too. The group's impact extends to all age groups, but most especially inspiring the female and the youth with empowerment and boss woman energy. Blackpink is a very dominant tone group which I prefer because other female Kpop groups have a more submissive tone which I also respect but I prefer the dominant tone more which is for me, that is Blackpink. Haters can argue with the wall. No one is stopping Blackpink. You can try to drag them down but the more you do that, the stronger Blackpink becomes and the fiercer the fandom becomes. Stay salty haters.

BASIC STREAMING RULES!:
Youtube

Elas tem personalidades diferente, mas conseguiram o que pouco conseguem suportar as diferença e harmoniza-las. But for me, Blackpink is the best girl group the world has ever had. Millions of fans from around the world think so too. The group's impact extends to all age groups, but most especially inspiring the female and the youth with empowerment and boss woman energy. Blackpink is a very dominant tone group which I prefer because other female Kpop groups have a more submissive tone which I also respect but I prefer the dominant tone more which is for me, that is Blackpink. Haters can argue with the wall. No one is stopping Blackpink. You can try to drag them down but the more you do that, the stronger Blackpink becomes and the fiercer the fandom becomes. Stay salty haters.

For those haters saying Teddy oppa copied the tune of Paganini: La Campanella well here is something you should know before saying that
For this Blackpink song and also for pink venom interpolation is used.
In popular music interpolation (also called a replayed sample) refers to using a melody-or portions of a melody (often with modified lyrics)from a previously recorded song but re-recording the melody instead of sampling it interpolation is often used when the artist or label who owns the place of music declines to license the sample, or if licensing the piece of music is considered too costly
